er the slime blood for close to 7 months now (activly timing golem spawns and contacting guilds who held Fear those days for about 4 of those months) and have NO slime blood to show for it.  I hardly call that easy.  I call that banging my head against the wall and getting nowhere fast.  Either people are greedy and want everything off the golems for themselves and don't take into account that I am trying NOT to gank them or I've just been horribly unlucky when guilds have been nice.</P><P>Pallys who pass level 52 have alternate means of obtaining epic via Gore and Tale as well as bards for the white/red scale and warriors for the red scale.  Why shouldn't necros get an alternate means of obtaining the slime blood when they've outgrown Fear?  Or, at the very least, add a mob that's a rare spawn in fear like the shissar and the only item on it's loot table is the slime blood.  Prefferably no drop without stats.  One thing I hate about epic items is the fact that some people want them just for stats.  I think all epic items should be no drop and statless.  I am sure mages could write books on how much they hate that the shoulder item they need insta clicks an uncharged lev.  I read about it on alla's and hardly ANYONE even mentioned that it was for the mage epic.  It was all posts about what classes would benifit the most from the stats/effect.</P><P>I hope something is done about this item.  I've worked on it for MANY months.  I know I've earned my epic.  I am just afraid that by the time I actually get it, it'll sit in a bag and come out when I need the effect.  I've offered up a number of very workable and fair solutions that wouldn't necissarily up the number of necro epics entering the game but would give more people a fair shot at their's.  I hope that one or more of these solutions could be futher entertained.</P><P>Reegor Mortees<BR>scaled Warlock</font></td>
