        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Here is my take on the Epic:</P><P>Useful to us as solo'ers?  yup -- free snare combined with a free fear from the Staff of the Dreaded Gaze means mana free killing solo.  Add to that a clickable lifetap ring and Velious Quest legs for free pet buffs, and you probably won't need to lich/leach anymore.</P><P>Useful in raids?  Not much.  The resist rate of darkness spells, combined with the added hate for being a Darkness line spell and you will quickly lose interest in using this at most raids.</P><P>Ability to get it?  High Difficulty...and here is why:</P><P>1.  Grouping as a Necro is still scarce.  No matter what they do for us group spell-wise (making them very costly to get) we will still be seen as the class that should be out solo'ing somewhere.  EQ is geared towards the cleric/warrior/chanter.  They have done some vey nice things for the Shaman, but rarely necessary outside of Slow.  They have admitted this time and time again, so arguing it is pointless.</P><P>2.  Guild Raid Priority - "Going into Chardok?  Ooooh!  Let's do a cleric epic raid and go after the Overking!...Oh, sorry...we don't have time to stop by and kill the Herbalist for you.  Maybe next time...  Anyone want to do Phinny or the Tangrin now?"  Plane of Air?  Most people don't understand the quality of gear here and say "Bah!  Nothing for me there!"  Fear raid?  "Let's do Hate, cus that's where all the good Cleric/Warrior gear drops..oh, hey!  We can get you the Eye of Inny for your Epic!...You already have that because you bought it off of a 7th level wizard?"  Let's face it, the guild is better off doing a great many other things then doing Necro epics.  Clickable rez, Clickable SoS, or a spell that is only for solo'ing for the most part?</P><P>3.  Buyable?  Sure, if you have the money and the trusting nature.  Ever hear of someone getting burned on a J-boots MQ?  Imagine dropping 30k+ to MQ part of your epic and having the guy LD on you and not come back.  Estimated cost of MQ, including scams...200k  I would rather have the big bad horse and 60k worth of Essense Emeralds.</P><P>So to those that say that this Epic is easy - either your main isn't a Necro or you need to think before you post.</P><P>Teroth Castille<BR>55 Defiler of Saryrn</P><P> </font></td>
