nsider the cast time on epic and dooming, I would have gained back at least 30 mana in the 4 sec difference in cast times.</P><P>So the value to me of an epic is 50 mana every 18 ticks. In other words its useless. When you factor in all the mobs that resist snare because of either 100% MR, or immune, or just plain ole resists, it's even more useless. Then factor in loss of hps in arch lich form while either swapping back and forth between heart and scythe, or the loss from not using heart period. It becomes pretty clear the epic isn't attractive to the high end game. And it certainly isn't worth the effort to save 50 mana every min and half and add 840 more damage. </P><P>So take your post about bitching and stuff it :) I made the decision to no longer attempt the quest after I looked at numbers, not because I could'nt do it. And I certainly didn't make the post because I'm jealous I don't have one. My post wasn't meant to be a whinning post, it was a legitimate question about work versus reward. </P><P>The reason I asked if you were even a necro, is because most of us know these numbers and that's why a bunch of us are unhappy with the epic, but you don't seem to grasp the concept to well. So I thought maybe you are a melee, and are focusing in on DPS only.</P><P>To beat a dead horse now :) When you factor in the mana savings, reduced cast time, and added damage from focus 3 and or magi summoned focus items, along with SCM AA skill. The epic becomes a token of the past, it's really not usefull (ok, it's not nearly as attractive as it once may have been) to our class anymore. If they really want to make it useful, make it a unresistable lifetap dot or dd, or a enhanced regen effect. Even with my item/natural regen at 28 a round arch lich can get hairy sometimes, I can't imagine how scary at times it gets for non Iksar necros. If that ever happened, I'd be the first person in line praising the epic, as well as first in line back to Fear, and PoS to get last items.</P><P></P><P> </font></td>
